Ultrasonographic screening for abdominal aortic aneurysm in an urban community. As part of the Birmingham Community Aneurysm Screening Project, 3500 men aged 65-75 years from 20 urban general practices were invited for aortic ultrasonographic screening at their own general practitioner's surgery 2669 (76.3 per cent) attended. Compliance rates varied between catchment areas, from 52.1 per cent for inner-city areas to 89.6 per cent for suburbs. Successful aortic imaging was achieved in 97.3 per cent of scans. Aortic diameter > 29 mm occurred in 219 patients (8.4 per cent) and 79 (3.0 per cent) with a diameter > 40 mm were referred for vascular surgical assessment